Here's an example of how to generate a table of contents automatically in a LATEX document:

1. First, you need to include the `bookmark` and `hyperref` packages in your preamble:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[english]{babel}
\usepackage{blindtext}
\usepackage{bookmark}
\usepackage{hyperref}

\begin{document}
```

2. Add `\setcounter{secnumdepth}{3}` to include section numbers up to subsubsection level:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[english]{babel}
\usepackage{blindtext}
\usepackage{bookmark}
\usepackage{hyperref}

\setcounter{secnumdepth}{3}

\begin{document}
```

3. Create some sections, subsections, and subsubsections in your document:

```latex
\tableofcontents

\section{Section 1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 1.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsubsection{Subsubsection 1.1.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 1.2}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 1.3}
\blindtext[2]

\section{Section 2}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 2.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsubsection{Subsubsection 2.1.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsubsection{Subsubsection 2.1.2}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 2.2}
\blindtext[2]

\section{Section 3}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 3.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsubsection{Subsubsection 3.1.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 3.2}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 3.3}
\blindtext[2]

\section{Section 4}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 4.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsubsection{Subsubsection 4.1.1}
\blindtext[2]

\subsubsection{Subsubsection 4.1.2}
\blindtext[2]

\subsection{Subsection 4.2}
\blindtext[2]

\section{Conclusion}
\blindtext[2]

\end{document}
```

4. Compile your document:

```latex
$ latex document.tex
$ latex document.tex
$ pdflatex document.tex
```

5. Your table of contents should now be automatically generated:

![table-of-contents](https://i.imgur.com/yjt5sOa.png)

Note that you may need to adjust the `\setcounter{secnumdepth}{3}` command to include section numbers up to the desired level (e.g., `\setcounter{secnumdepth}{2}` for just sections and subsections). Also, the `bookmark` and `hyperref` packages are optional, but they provide bookmarks and hyperlinks in your PDF document, respectively.

